# Vendure Dashboard (React UI) Plugin Development Rules

This project uses **Vendure v3 Dashboard** (React-based, NOT Angular). Dashboard extensions live inside each plugin's `dashboard/` directory and are registered via `dashboard: './dashboard/index.tsx'` in the `@VendurePlugin` decorator.

## Technology Stack

- **React** (hooks-based, functional components only)
- **@vendure/dashboard** - all layout, form, and page components
- **@tanstack/react-router** - routing (`useNavigate`, `Link`, `useParams`)
- **@tanstack/react-query** - data fetching (`useQuery`, `useMutation`, `useQueryClient`)
- **sonner** - toast notifications (`toast.success()`, `toast.error()`)
- **lucide-react** - icons
- **react-hook-form** - form state management (integrated into `useDetailPage`)
- **@/gql** - typed GraphQL operations via codegen (aliased to `./src/gql/graphql.ts`)

---

## Dashboard Directory Structure

```
src/plugins/<plugin-name>/dashboard/
  ├── index.tsx                    # Extension entry point (defineDashboardExtension)
  ├── <entity>.graphql.ts          # GraphQL fragments, queries, mutations
  ├── <entity>-list.tsx            # List page component
  ├── <entity>-detail.tsx          # Detail/create/edit page component
  └── components/
      ├── <entity>-bulk-actions.tsx # Bulk action components (optional)
      └── <other-components>.tsx   # Any additional UI components
```

---

## Extension Entry Point (index.tsx)

```tsx
import { defineDashboardExtension } from '@vendure/dashboard';
import { SomeIcon } from 'lucide-react';
import { myEntityList } from './<entity>-list';
import { myEntityDetail } from './<entity>-detail';
import { DeleteBulkAction } from './components/<entity>-bulk-actions';

defineDashboardExtension({
    // Create a new nav section (optional - use existing ones if appropriate)
    navSections: [
        {
            id: 'my-section',
            title: 'My Section',
            icon: SomeIcon,
            order: 550,  // Controls position in sidebar
        },
    ],
    // Register page routes
    routes: [myEntityList, myEntityDetail],
    // Register bulk actions for list pages
    dataTables: [
        {
            pageId: '<entity>-list',  // Must match the ListPage pageId
            bulkActions: [
                {
                    order: 100,
                    component: DeleteBulkAction,
                },
            ],
        },
    ],
});
```

Available extension options:
- `navSections` - Create new sidebar sections
- `routes` - Add new page routes
- `dataTables` - Add bulk actions to list pages
- `pageBlocks` - Inject UI into existing detail pages
- `actionBarItems` - Add buttons to existing page action bars
- `customFormComponents` - Register custom form input components

### Using existing nav sections

Built-in section IDs: `'catalog'`, `'sales'`, `'marketing'`, `'customers'`, `'settings'`, `'system'`

```tsx
navMenuItem: {
    sectionId: 'marketing',  // Use existing section
    id: 'my-entity',
    title: 'My Entity',
    url: '/my-entity',
    requiresPermission: 'ReadMyEntity',
},
```

