## Bulk Actions (components/<entity>-bulk-actions.tsx)

```tsx
import { BulkActionComponent, DataTableBulkActionItem, api } from '@vendure/dashboard';
import { Trash2 } from 'lucide-react';
import { useMutation, useQueryClient } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { toast } from 'sonner';
import { deleteMyEntityMutation } from '../<entity>.graphql';

export const DeleteBulkAction: BulkActionComponent = ({ selection, table }) => {
    const queryClient = useQueryClient();
    const { mutateAsync } = useMutation({
        mutationFn: (ids: string[]) =>
            api.mutate(deleteMyEntityMutation, { ids }),
    });

    return (
        <DataTableBulkActionItem
            label="Delete"
            icon={Trash2}
            requiresPermission={['DeleteMyEntity']}
            confirmationText={`Delete ${selection.length} item(s)?`}
            onClick={async () => {
                const ids = selection.map(row => row.id);
                try {
                    await mutateAsync(ids);
                    toast.success(`Deleted ${ids.length} item(s)`);
                    table.resetRowSelection();
                    await queryClient.invalidateQueries();
                } catch (e) {
                    toast.error('Failed to delete items');
                }
            }}
        />
    );
};
```

Rules:
- Bulk action components receive `{ selection, table }` props
- Use `api.mutate()` from `@vendure/dashboard` for mutations
- Use `api.query()` for queries
- ALWAYS invalidate queries after mutations: `queryClient.invalidateQueries()`
- ALWAYS reset row selection after bulk action: `table.resetRowSelection()`
- Use `requiresPermission` array on `DataTableBulkActionItem`

---

## Table Components (IMPORTANT)

When displaying tabular data in dashboard extensions, **ALWAYS use table components from `@vendure/dashboard`**. DO NOT use raw HTML `<table>` elements or third-party table libraries. There are three levels of table abstraction available, listed from highest to lowest level:

### 1. `ListPage` (Preferred for standard list views)

The highest-level abstraction. Auto-generates columns from a GraphQL list query, with built-in search, filtering, sorting, pagination, and bulk action support. **Use this for any standard entity list page.**

```tsx
import { ListPage, DetailPageButton } from '@vendure/dashboard';

<ListPage
    pageId="my-entity-list"
    title="My Entities"
    listQuery={getMyEntityListQuery}
    route={route}
    defaultVisibility={{ id: false, languageCode: false, translations: false }}
    onSearchTermChange={searchTerm => ({ title: { contains: searchTerm } })}
    customizeColumns={{
        title: {
            cell: ({ row }) => (
                <DetailPageButton id={row.original.id} label={row.original.title} />
            ),
        },
    }}
>
    {/* Action bar children */}
</ListPage>
```

### 2. `DataTable` (For custom/embedded tables)

A mid-level component that uses `@tanstack/react-table` column definitions. **Use this when embedding a table inside a detail page, custom page, or any non-standard list view** (e.g., a sub-table of related items within a detail page).

```tsx
import { DataTable } from '@vendure/dashboard';
import { createColumnHelper } from '@tanstack/react-table';

type MyItem = { id: string; name: string; status: string };
const columnHelper = createColumnHelper<MyItem>();

const columns = [
    columnHelper.accessor('name', {
        header: 'Name',
        cell: info => <span className="font-medium">{info.getValue()}</span>,
    }),
    columnHelper.accessor('status', {
        header: 'Status',
        cell: info => <span>{info.getValue()}</span>,
    }),
    columnHelper.display({
        id: 'actions',
        header: () => <div className="text-right">Actions</div>,
        cell: ({ row }) => (
            <div className="flex items-center gap-2 justify-end">
                <Button variant="ghost" size="sm" onClick={() => handleEdit(row.original)}>
                    Edit
                </Button>
            </div>
        ),
    }),
];

// In JSX:
<DataTable
    columns={columns}
    data={items}
    totalItems={totalItems}
    isLoading={isLoading}
    page={currentPage}
    itemsPerPage={itemsPerPage}
    onPageChange={(_, page, perPage) => {
        setCurrentPage(page);
        setItemsPerPage(perPage);
    }}
/>
```

Props:
- `columns` - Column definitions from `createColumnHelper` (`@tanstack/react-table`)
- `data` - Array of row data
- `totalItems` - Total count for pagination
- `isLoading` - Loading state
- `page` - Current page number
- `itemsPerPage` - Items per page
- `onPageChange` - Callback `(event, page, perPage) => void`

### 3. `Table` primitives (For fully custom layouts)

Low-level shadcn/ui-style table primitives. **Use only when `ListPage` and `DataTable` don't fit** (e.g., a simple read-only table with no pagination, or a highly custom layout).

```tsx
import {
    Table,
    TableHeader,
    TableBody,
    TableRow,
    TableHead,
    TableCell,
} from '@vendure/dashboard';

<Table>
    <TableHeader>
        <TableRow>
            <TableHead>Name</TableHead>
            <TableHead>Status</TableHead>
            <TableHead>Created</TableHead>
        </TableRow>
    </TableHeader>
    <TableBody>
        {items.map(item => (
            <TableRow key={item.id}>
                <TableCell>{item.name}</TableCell>
                <TableCell>{item.status}</TableCell>
                <TableCell>{item.createdAt}</TableCell>
            </TableRow>
        ))}
    </TableBody>
</Table>
```

### Which table to use?

| Scenario | Component |
|----------|-----------|
| Standard entity list page with search/filter/sort/pagination | `ListPage` |
| Embedded table inside a detail page or custom page | `DataTable` |
| Simple read-only table, no pagination needed | `Table` primitives |
| **Raw HTML `<table>`** | **NEVER - use one of the above instead** |

Rules:
- **ALWAYS import table components from `@vendure/dashboard`** - never use raw HTML `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<tr>`, `<th>`, `<td>` elements
- **Prefer `ListPage`** for any standard list view - it handles search, filtering, sorting, pagination, and bulk actions automatically
- **Use `DataTable`** when you need a table embedded inside another page (e.g., a list of applications inside a job posting detail page)
- **Use `Table` primitives** only when `ListPage` and `DataTable` are not suitable for the layout
- When using `DataTable`, define columns with `createColumnHelper` from `@tanstack/react-table` and manage pagination state manually
- When using `DataTable`, wrap column definitions in `useMemo` to avoid unnecessary re-renders

