## Permission Guards (REQUIRED)

Every dashboard extension MUST enforce permissions in **3 locations**. Failing to add any of these means unauthorized admin users can access or modify the entity.

### 1. Nav Menu Item (`requiresPermission`)

Controls whether the nav link is visible to the current admin user.

```tsx
// In <entity>-list.tsx
navMenuItem: {
    sectionId: 'my-section',
    id: 'my-entity-list',
    url: '/my-entity',
    title: 'My Entities',
    requiresPermission: 'MyPermission',  // REQUIRED
},
```

### 2. Detail Page Submit Button (`<PermissionGuard>`)

Hides the Create/Update button from unauthorized users. Import `PermissionGuard` from `@vendure/dashboard`.

```tsx
// In <entity>-detail.tsx
import { PermissionGuard } from '@vendure/dashboard';

<PageActionBarRight>
    <PermissionGuard requires={['MyPermission']}>
        <Button type="submit" disabled={!form.formState.isDirty || isPending}>
            {creatingNewEntity ? 'Create' : 'Update'}
        </Button>
    </PermissionGuard>
</PageActionBarRight>
```

### 3. Bulk Action (`requiresPermission`)

Controls whether the bulk action (e.g., delete) is available to the current admin user.

```tsx
// In components/<entity>-bulk-actions.tsx
<DataTableBulkActionItem
    label="Delete"
    icon={Trash2}
    requiresPermission={['MyPermission']}  // REQUIRED
    confirmationText={`Delete ${selection.length} item(s)?`}
    onClick={handleDelete}
/>
```

**Important:** The permission name used in the dashboard (e.g., `'MyPermission'`) must match the `name` defined in the plugin's `PermissionDefinition` (in `constants.ts`).

